text: Arne Røgden (born May 16, 1917 - January 1, 2002) was a Norwegian bobsledder who competed during the 1950s. Competing in two Winter Olympics, he earned his best finish of 11th in the four-man event at Cortina d'Ampezzo in 1956. He was born in Oslo and died in Bærum. ==References== *1952 bobsleigh four-man results *1956 bobsleigh two-man results *1956 bobsleigh four-man results *Bobsleigh four-man results: 1948-64.
